  "interpretation": [
    "The direct decoder path is the correct harness for Metal kernel iteration when the macOS ONNX Runtime package is missing libonnxruntime_providers_shared.dylib.",
    "Lowering the fused conv1d threshold from 8192 to 4096 improves short and medium synthetic decoder shapes without changing decoder output in the tested frames.",
    "FP32 remains slightly faster than FP16 in this latest direct decoder run, so further Metal conv1d scheduling work is still warranted before claiming an end-to-end FP16 performance win."
